    • Method Detail

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        Returns this development line's identifier or null if no identifier has been set.

        Development line ids are unique per project area.

        In order for this item to be saved to the repository this field must have a non-null value, so it is safe to assume that this method will not return null if it is an immutable copy fetched from the repository. It is possible for an incomplete/invalid working copy, however, to return null.

        Returns:
        the development line's identifier or null

      • setId

        void setId(java.lang.String id)
        Sets this development line's identifier.
        Parameters:
        id - the new identifier

      • getLabel

        java.lang.String getLabel()
        This convenience method returns the name of this line if the name is not null and is not a whitespace string. Otherwise it returns this line's id, which may be null if this item is a working copy (@see getId().
        Returns:
        the name or id of this development line or null

      • getProjectArea

        IProjectAreaHandle getProjectArea()
        Returns the project area which contains this development line or null if no project area has been set.

        In order for this item to be saved to the repository this field must have a non-null value, so it is safe to assume that this method will not return null if it is an immutable copy fetched from the repository. It is possible for an incomplete/invalid working copy, however, to return null.

        Returns:
        the project area which contains this development line

      • setProjectArea

        void setProjectArea(IProjectAreaHandle projectArea)
        Sets this development line's project area. In order to complete the bi-directional relationship, callers must also add this development line to the project area.
        Parameters:
        projectArea - the handle of the project area

      • insertIterationAfter

        void insertIterationAfter(IIterationHandle iteration,
                        IIterationHandle anchor)
        Adds the iteration identified by the given handle into the list of children right of the given anchor. In order to complete the bi-directional relationship, callers must also set this development line on the given iteration. If the given iteration is already an iteration of this development line, this method does not have any effect. If the anchor is null the iteration is added at the beginning of the list.
        Parameters:
        iteration - a handle for the iteration
        anchor - the anchor after which to insert the iteration or null

      • addIteration

        void addIteration(IIterationHandle iteration)
        Adds the iteration identified by the given handle at the end of the list of children. In order to complete the bi-directional relationship, callers must also set this development line on the given iteration. If the given iteration is already an iteration of this development line, this method does not have any effect.
        Parameters:
        iteration - a handle for the iteration

      • removeIteration

        void removeIteration(IIterationHandle iteration)
        Removes the iteration identified by the given handle from the list of iterations. If the iteration does not belong to this development line, this method does not have any effect. In order to ensure the consistency of the bi-directional relationship, the caller has also to remove the development line from the iteration.
        Parameters:
        iteration - a handle to the iteration

        this development line's current iteration
